  "text": "Here, d(C i , j) is the distance between an elected CH and its neighbours. 3. Packet Drop Probability (PDP): Packet Drop Probability characterises the transmission quality of a link between a node and an elected CH. The packet drop in a network is attributed to the presence of attenuation, interference, noise etc. To calculate the same, uniform random distribution [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] is used in this work. The packet drop probability is dependent on the distance between a node m and an elected CH C i (d(C i , m)) which is given in equation [CITATION_3] . If the link probability is larger than PDP, then the packet is supposed to be successfully delivered, else it will be dropped.",
